					I started my journey quite early on attempting to understand big books on HTML from the library. In highschool I was manipulating webpages and graphics on social sites for friends and myself. After trying out some Java and C++ courses in my under grad I changed my studies over to software engineering. Completed a diploma in Digital Design & Development from British Columbia Institute of Technology with disstinction.
				</p>
				<h3>Skills</h3>
				<p>
					HTML5, CSS3, Javascript, Vue, Nodejs, CouchDB (NoSQL)
				</p>
				<h3>Experience</h3>
